Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.77,0:02:58.33,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,{\an8}Mista!\N Hurry up and pierce your Stand with this arrow!{Copy-paste from the latest version of 35's script... Double-check to make sure it matches the final version. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.33,0:03:01.41,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,What? \NRequiem just started charging at us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.95,0:03:04.24,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno! \NStop Requiem!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.24,0:03:05.49,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I can't! \NIt's too far away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.12,0:03:09.62,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Wha{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.62,0:03:11.21,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,My gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.21,0:03:12.77,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What's going on, Mista?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.77,0:03:14.17,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,It's because he's touching the arrow!{Okay the way this is set up it's confusing. It looks like she's addressing Mista but she's actually continuing her OWN previous thought about Requiem heading towards them, and so the "he" here is Polnareff. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.17,0:03:16.80,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,No way!\N Why did it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:18.42,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Let go of it, Mr. Polnareff!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.42,0:03:20.30,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Let go of the arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.73,0:03:30.23,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Glad I took that cop's Beretta, just in case.{"For a situation like this"? Sounds rather stiff to me... Wouldn't "just in case" be better? -Starfish}{Just in case would necessitate a comma, so I prefer this. -J}{So then add a heckin' comma, don't be doin' me a frighten -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.23,0:03:32.15,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,But what the hell, Pistols?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.15,0:03:34.81,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Why did my revolver break out of nowhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:38.39,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,M-Maybe the boss got close?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.32,0:03:42.77,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Idiot!\N Think before ya run yer mouth, Number Five!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.77,0:03:48.19,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,You sayin' you saw someone get close to us \N in this big open space?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.19,0:03:51.04,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,None of us saw anyone when the revolver broke!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:52.57,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,The metal's worn down!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.57,0:03:55.38,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,He's been using it too much recently! {"his gun" implies that there's someone else's gun too -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:57.45,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,The cylinder axis broke!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.45,0:04:01.01,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,We haven't had time to do any \N maintenance or inspections!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.01,0:04:02.47,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.68,0:04:16.21,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What the hell is this thing's problem? \NIt's going right for m-me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.21,0:04:19.22,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,No, Mista.\N It's coming for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.22,0:04:21.90,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Even though it has the arrow back...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.90,0:04:23.45,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Gold Experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.05,0:04:34.04,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Requiem plans to end me{It's more like "put an utter end to me"... ergo, kill him. -Starfish} \Nsince I touched the arrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.04,0:04:34.92,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Run, Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.37,0:04:39.09,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Reload, Pistols! \NReload the gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:42.48,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,This isn't a revolver! \NWe need another cartridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.48,0:04:44.59,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,It's gonna take time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:48.73,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,I-It's no use...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.73,0:04:49.72,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,I'm done for...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.47,0:04:58.77,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I'm throwing him!\N Giorno, catch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.14,0:05:01.73,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I'm gonna toss you the tortoise!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.12,0:05:08.37,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Mr. Polnareff!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.58,0:05:24.30,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You okay, Mr. Polnareff?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:27.64,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,He's okay. B-But... how?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.21,0:05:32.69,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Mista, do you remember what \NI said back at the Colosseum?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.73,0:05:38.40,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,I said that Requiem's ability \Nhad potential even I wasn't aware of. {I'm... honestly not sure which line he's referring to here. Maybe the line at 18:50 in episode 34? -J}{Yeah it's almost certainly that. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.89,0:05:40.79,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,But I'm beginning to understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.79,0:05:44.30,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Requiem stopped because the time has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.30,0:05:46.49,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,The time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.49,0:05:47.65,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.65,0:05:49.70,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,I can tell because...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:51.59,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,...my body has started to change!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.59,0:05:54.20,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,That's why it stopped trying to kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.80,0:05:59.41,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,This is the true reason Requiem went berserk!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.41,0:06:07.05,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,The ability to force living beings to swap souls; \Nergo, the ability to turn them into something else!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.58,0:06:10.51,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,The prelude has ended, \Nnow the main piece is beginning to play...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.83,0:06:13.93,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,...which is why it gave up on killing me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.93,0:06:19.13,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,4.5 billion years' worth of history\N of the creatures of the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.13,0:06:22.27,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,...is about to be overwritten in just a few short hours!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.27,0:06:23.40,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,All of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:25.04,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.04,0:06:28.61,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,So this is the true terror of Requiem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.61,0:06:29.86,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,But even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.77,0:06:33.76,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Thanks to them, I see it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.76,0:06:36.33,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I've begun to understand the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.89,0:06:40.75,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I'm on the verge of figuring out \Nhow to steal the arrow from Requiem!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.75,0:06:42.71,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I know what I must do!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.06,0:06:46.38,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Wh-What the hell is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:48.47,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What's up with this ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:51.42,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,How far has this damn thing spread?{Yup; He's literally asking in the scope of the entire planet -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.42,0:06:54.89,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,They don't look as if they're dying or in pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.89,0:06:57.71,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,They just have blank stares on their faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.71,0:07:02.53,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,But... I'm afraid of my mind\N transforming into something else...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.53,0:07:08.46,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Afraid that little by little, \Nmy body and mind will disappear without a trace...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.56,0:07:10.15,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.15,0:07:12.70,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I-I'm fine! But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.05,0:07:15.74,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,The time is already upon us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.74,0:07:19.91,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,It won't play out the same for everyone,\N but soon we'll all be affected.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.91,0:07:23.88,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,So we don't have much time, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:27.07,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Polnareff! \NThis is happening because you brought the arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.07,0:07:29.65,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,This is the exact opposite of\N what we needed to defeat the boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.65,0:07:31.39,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Way to tighten the noose on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.39,0:07:34.86,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Enough!\N No one could have predicted this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.86,0:07:37.97,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We need to focus on\N finding a way to defeat Requiem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.23,0:07:45.77,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Yes! Get closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.77,0:07:47.53,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Get closer to Requiem!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.00,0:07:53.76,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I'll be able to see all of Requiem's secrets \Nif we only get a bit closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.76,0:07:58.49,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,The arrow's power will become mine, \Nand the world will bend to my whims!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.49,0:07:59.66,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,After it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.66,0:08:00.47,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.47,0:08:02.29,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Don't move, Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.98,0:08:04.91,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Trish and Buccellati, stay right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.91,0:08:05.88,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.88,0:08:06.78,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Wha{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.32,0:08:09.26,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I just told you not to move, Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.26,0:08:11.67,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We can catch up to Requiem after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.67,0:08:13.97,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What the hell? \NShut up, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:16.47,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,My body's already disappearing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.81,0:08:19.27,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I picked up your revolver.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.27,0:08:22.27,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The one that you said broke a moment ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:26.84,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This broken piece doesn't match up \Ncorrectly with the rest of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.84,0:08:30.49,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,If it broke due to the metal becoming worn,\N the pieces should still fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.49,0:08:33.45,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno, what are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.81,0:08:35.67,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You can't move either, Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:37.70,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We need to keep our distance from each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.70,0:08:40.33,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Come on! \NRequiem is getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.33,0:08:45.23,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,If the Pistols said the metal was worn out, \Nthen the metal was worn out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.23,0:08:47.43,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I have this new Beretta now, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.43,0:08:51.70,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,The pieces don't match up since part of it flew off!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.70,0:08:53.22,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.75,0:08:56.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,But perhaps there's more to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.37,0:08:59.87,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We'll know once we see this lost piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.56,0:09:02.98,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Gold Experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.98,0:09:05.71,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I imbued part of the gun with life and set it loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.71,0:09:10.44,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Moles are essentially blind, \Nbut their sense of smell is unparalleled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.21,0:09:15.32,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It seems to have returned with the lost piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.74,0:09:23.17,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,H-Hey, hold on a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.17,0:09:27.08,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Are you saying someone broke my gun apart by force?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.08,0:09:31.18,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Listen to me! \NThe Pistols and I are sure about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.18,0:09:33.81,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,There's nobody in this square who got anywhere close to{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.81,0:09:36.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Precisely. No one did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.37,0:09:38.19,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We need to keep our distance from each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.19,0:09:40.49,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...since his range is only a few meters!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.74,0:09:43.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.69,0:09:47.93,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No one was near Narancia when he was attacked, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.93,0:09:50.65,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No one... other than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.83,0:09:58.28,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Mr. Polnareff, if your hypothesis{I have an odd fixation with not using "theory" in non-scientific contexts. -Starfish} is correct \Nand the boss does indeed have two personalities...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.28,0:10:01.12,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...then his mind should be capable \Nof freely moving in and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.87,0:10:05.08,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Diavolo has latched on to one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.08,0:10:05.85,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Wha{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.48,0:10:11.72,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,While he's hidden, Trish can't sense his presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.72,0:10:16.33,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,He intends to remain in hiding \Nuntil we've secured the arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.33,0:10:19.76,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's why he only appeared for\N a brief moment to destroy the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.87,0:10:24.46,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,H-Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.46,0:10:27.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I know I'm repeating myself, \Nbut stay away, Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.47,0:10:29.15,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Stay out of his range!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.15,0:10:31.73,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,My gun was destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.43,0:10:35.90,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You're the closest person to your gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:37.11,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I-It...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.43,0:10:38.97,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's not me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.97,0:10:42.46,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,O-Oh, yeah! \NWhen Narancia was attacked...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.46,0:10:45.08,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...the closest person to him was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.83,0:10:52.79,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Damn. I need to act...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.38,0:10:56.30,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Requiem is getting away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.30,0:11:00.25,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,This newcomer, Giorno Giovanna...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.25,0:11:03.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,He's hiding within one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.97,0:11:07.56,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,But even so, we possess one advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:11.15,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Diavolo can make King Crimson appear...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.15,0:11:14.44,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...but he doesn't have complete control \Nover the body he's currently inhabiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.88,0:11:22.83,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,If he had total control, \Nhe wouldn't be hiding from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.83,0:11:27.70,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The only reason we're still alive is because he can't manifest and freely move around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.42,0:11:31.42,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We essentially have him cornered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.75,0:11:34.39,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's the tortoise!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.39,0:11:37.25,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It was the closest one to my revolver!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.25,0:11:39.37,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Polnareff is the one who's possessed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.37,0:11:40.59,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It isn't him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.59,0:11:44.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Requiem nearly killed Mr. Polnareff earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.37,0:11:46.75,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...since the boss destroyed the revolver.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.39,0:11:51.06,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The boss wouldn't allow the body \Nhe's inhabiting to be put in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.39,0:11:52.56,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.03,0:11:56.68,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I only sense one being's life energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.68,0:11:59.32,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,A single soul lies within this tortoise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.32,0:12:02.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You can tell that, Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.27,0:12:07.29,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Only if I get close enough to touch their body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.29,0:12:09.15,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,How can you be sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.15,0:12:11.41,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Life energy exists in clusters.{I basically copied this phrasing from the manga TL... It's clearer than CR's "Life force is a mass", anyway. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.41,0:12:14.50,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,If I can touch someone, I can tell how many there are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.20,0:12:16.98,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,There's no other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.98,0:12:19.74,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I have to touch each one of you to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.74,0:12:24.18,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But how will you get closer?\N You'll enter King Crimson's range.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.76,0:12:32.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Mr. Polnareff taught me \Nhow to detect King Crimson.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.37,0:12:36.98,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The number of droplets increasing\N indicates the moment time has been skipped!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.90,0:12:39.38,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.38,0:12:42.67,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,But whether or not you can \Navoid his attack is a matter of luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.23,0:12:47.16,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,...as is whether you'll be able \Nto dodge it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.87,0:12:55.03,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's definitely not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.03,0:12:59.08,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I was the farthest away when he got Narancia...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.63,0:13:03.06,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Then I'll check you first\Nso we can be at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.06,0:13:03.76,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.09,0:13:07.22,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Don't move!\N Stay away from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.66,0:13:10.18,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,B-Back off!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.52,0:13:16.43,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What'll happen to me if Diavolo is inside {\i1}you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.41,0:13:21.03,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,When Narancia died,\N this body was an empty husk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.00,0:13:27.11,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,My soul was able to travel from \NNarancia's body into my own, but it was empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.13,0:13:31.60,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,There's no chance that he's possessing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.43,0:13:34.66,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.66,0:13:37.18,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,That's what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.18,0:13:40.25,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I can't confirm if your ability works.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.93,0:13:42.37,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,And anyway, Giorno...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.37,0:13:45.97,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...do you have a way of knowing \Nfor sure that you only have one soul?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:49.87,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You can't check yourself with \Nyour own ability, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.87,0:13:53.31,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Mista, we can't go after the \Narrow unless we find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.31,0:13:55.52,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Come any closer and I'll blow your limbs off!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.90,0:14:02.05,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.05,0:14:07.32,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Check me first, Giorno.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.69,0:14:10.99,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Hurry and do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.99,0:14:13.70,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We're losing precious time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.70,0:14:18.96,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,As you said, we have the boss cornered \Ndepending on how you look at our situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.96,0:14:20.81,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,There's no other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.81,0:14:21.92,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.92,0:14:24.05,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,We need to do this now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.54,0:14:35.76,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Someone's going to be attacked...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.76,0:14:38.12,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,If we get closer to one another...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.19,0:14:56.31,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.31,0:14:57.33,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,It's Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.33,0:14:59.17,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,He was possessed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.17,0:15:00.17,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Spice Gi{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.17,0:15:01.21,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,No, Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.21,0:15:02.17,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.35,0:15:07.55,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He moved your body closer to me in a single moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.59,0:15:12.91,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for this moment, my daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.91,0:15:16.15,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,The moment you would unleash your Stand!
Comment: 0,0:15:19.02,0:15:19.06,Main,,0,0,0,,C
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.74,0:15:25.32,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,My daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:32.12,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,If you hadn't revealed your Stand, \NI might still be in a bind...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.12,0:15:34.03,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Sticky Fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.87,0:15:41.33,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,By grabbing your Stand,\N I can manipulate your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.81,0:15:45.67,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Now at least I can make this body flee.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.67,0:15:48.44,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He's going to attack! \NBrace yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.44,0:15:49.71,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Time is going to be er{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.94,0:15:52.57,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Wha{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.57,0:15:54.01,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.10,0:15:58.47,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Why did he run away without attacking us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.47,0:16:04.15,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Through observation, he's already found\N a way to get the arrow away from Requiem!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.47,0:16:07.48,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We have no time! \NThis takes priority!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.48,0:16:08.81,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mista, fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.81,0:16:10.82,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Don't let him beat us to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.49,0:16:15.29,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Quit wasting time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.29,0:16:18.04,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You can't hesitate just because it's your own body!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.04,0:16:19.66,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's not that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.66,0:16:21.87,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I already fired, Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.28,0:16:26.46,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I already... fired six shots...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.60,0:16:39.22,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He's making time leaps as he runs!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.56,0:16:42.56,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He predicted the trajectory of the bullets!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.88,0:16:46.48,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,After him! \NIf he gets the arrow, it's all over!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.08,0:16:54.74,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Its shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.74,0:16:57.78,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,That is what prevents anyone from touching the arrow. {earlier it was "why" instead of "what", which seems wrong. The shadow is a thing, not a reason -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.78,0:17:01.08,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,If I'm understanding this correctly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:09.17,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...when I move, Requiem's shadow moves in\N the opposite direction from me, independent of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.73,0:17:11.13,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.53,0:17:16.26,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...to that man, it should appear as though the shadow is stretching toward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.26,0:17:21.11,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,In Buccellati's eyes, the shadow is \Nstretching in front of Requiem.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.11,0:17:21.93,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,So logically...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.93,0:17:26.55,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...every person perceives the shadow differently!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.55,0:17:28.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That is Requiem's secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.69,0:17:33.19,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This is how it controls people's souls!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.19,0:17:35.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's the very shadow of one's soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.69,0:17:39.49,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Requiem itself is the shadow of my soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.49,0:17:43.79,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That's why attacking it is to attack yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.17,0:17:47.45,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I can retrieve the arrow if I eliminate the shadow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.45,0:17:48.54,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Furthermore...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.54,0:17:53.21,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,If my soul has a shadow,\N then my light must exist somewhere, as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.21,0:17:55.25,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He still doesn't have the arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.25,0:17:56.59,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Let's rush him, Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.32,0:18:01.10,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The light source is behind my mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.79,0:18:08.44,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He just destroyed something behind his head!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.44,0:18:10.20,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What did he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.30,0:18:12.98,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I have it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.98,0:18:17.11,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I, Diavolo, now have the arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.11,0:18:23.91,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,If Diavolo found a way to retrieve the arrow, then we should take advantage of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.23,0:18:31.00,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The droplets of blood from him \Ntearing off my arm are now a simple material...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.46,0:18:34.76,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Gold Experience shall now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.73,0:18:38.53,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...manifest!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.53,0:18:39.64,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,These ants!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.64,0:18:41.55,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What have they done to the arrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.61,0:18:45.23,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,So far it's working...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.23,0:18:46.66,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I need to go...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.66,0:18:48.69,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I can't waste time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.52,0:18:53.22,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Blast the arrow away from him! \NDon't let him grab it, Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.22,0:18:54.73,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I'm already shooting!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.39,0:18:58.38,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.38,0:19:00.76,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Even if he can predict them,\N look at the distance between us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.76,0:19:05.08,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He can only knock the ones \Ncoming at him out of their trajectory!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.08,0:19:09.00,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,The rest of you knock that arrow back \Nand bring it to me, Pistols!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.38,0:19:17.35,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,H-He'd already thrown...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.35,0:19:18.99,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,...someone into the air!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.99,0:19:23.30,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,He knew where the bullets would land \Nand made 'em push the arrow back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:26.07,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,The trash ability of a trash underling...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.07,0:19:31.88,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,It is utterly impossible for your feeble intellect \N to surpass King Crimson's predictions. {jesus calm down dude}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.88,0:19:34.09,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You will never break through!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.09,0:19:36.38,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You're nothing but trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.38,0:19:38.11,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I will admit though, Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.11,0:19:42.70,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Your team has made me sweat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.70,0:19:47.64,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I never dreamed you would be \Nfoolish enough to betray the organization...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.64,0:19:51.83,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...nor did I ever imagine you would\N uncover my true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.83,0:19:58.03,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,However!\N The fact that I've learned of this arrow's true power is a gift!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.03,0:20:01.98,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,A gift granted to me by fate\N for overcoming my past!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.98,0:20:03.76,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I need more ammo, Pistols!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.76,0:20:05.52,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,We already told you, Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.52,0:20:09.56,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Reloading the cartridge takes time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.56,0:20:12.86,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,W-We're done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.13,0:20:20.78,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Wh-What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.17,0:20:23.95,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Spice... Girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.59,0:20:28.81,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,You didn't deflect Mista's bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.81,0:20:31.85,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I just softened them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.85,0:20:36.54,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,The bullets stuck to your hand\N like chewing gum and stretched out...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.05,0:20:40.34,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...and the elastic force \Nmade them snap back through your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.34,0:20:43.26,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Trish... You're still conscious!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.26,0:20:46.18,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I'm going to rise above this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.18,0:20:51.91,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I refuse to live in fear and run away\N from the fate you've passed on to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.91,0:20:56.44,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,If it's in my way, I'll rise above it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.89,0:21:00.15,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,The arrow's flying right at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.92,0:21:02.57,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I'm the closest!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.57,0:21:04.53,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He can't get past me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.89,0:21:08.24,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Even if he predicts where \Nit'll fall and erases time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.24,0:21:10.70,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...I'll still be closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.70,0:21:13.70,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,If only... my daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.70,0:21:16.62,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...if only you had never been born...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.62,0:21:20.32,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Fear truly does stem from the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.32,0:21:25.03,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You have angered me greatly!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.45,0:21:32.35,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.06,0:21:39.41,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You said you would rise above, did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.41,0:21:44.41,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You were right, Trish. \NNow you can rise above not only your past...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.03,0:21:47.16,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...but above their heads as well. {what? -G}{He's basically making a play on words here: She can OVERCOME her past... and she can PHYSICALLY GO ABOVE the others' heads, allowing him to beat them to catching the arrow. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.37,0:21:52.59,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish!
